#. <section class="sutta" id="sn12.53"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn12.53:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 12"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 12"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn12.53:0.2"
msgid "6. Dukkhavagga"
msgstr "6. Suffering"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn12.53:0.3"
msgid "53. Saṃyojanasutta"
msgstr "53. Fetters"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli2.86"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.53:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthiyaṃ viharati."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Saṃyojaniyesu, bhikkhave, dhammesu assādānupassino viharato taṇhā "
"pavaḍḍhati."
msgstr ""
"“There are things that are prone to being fettered. When you concentrate on "
"the gratification provided by these things, your craving grows."

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.3"
msgid "Taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ;"
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping."

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.4"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo;"
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence."

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.5"
msgid "bhavapaccayā jāti;"
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth."

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.6"
msgid "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti."
msgstr ""
"Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, "
"sadness, and distress to come to be."

msgctxt "sn12.53:1.7"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.53:2.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, telañca paṭicca vaṭṭiñca paṭicca telappadīpo jhāyeyya."
msgstr "Suppose an oil lamp depended on oil and a wick to burn."

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.2"
msgid "Tatra puriso kālena kālaṃ telaṃ āsiñceyya vaṭṭiṃ upasaṃhareyya."
msgstr "And from time to time someone would pour oil in and adjust the wick."

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.3"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, telappadīpo tadāhāro tadupādāno ciraṃ dīghamaddhānaṃ "
"jaleyya."
msgstr "Fueled and sustained by that, the oil lamp would burn for a long time."

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyesu dhammesu assādānupassino viharato "
"taṇhā pavaḍḍhati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are things that are prone to being fettered. When you "
"concentrate on the gratification provided by these things, your craving "
"grows."

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.5"
msgid "Taṇhāpaccayā upādānaṃ;"
msgstr "Craving is a condition for grasping."

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.6"
msgid "upādānapaccayā bhavo;"
msgstr "Grasping is a condition for continued existence."

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.7"
msgid "bhavapaccayā jāti;"
msgstr "Continued existence is a condition for rebirth."

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.8"
msgid "jātipaccayā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā sambhavanti."
msgstr ""
"Rebirth is a condition for old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, "
"sadness, and distress to come to be."

msgctxt "sn12.53:2.9"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa samudayo hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering originates."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.53:3.1"
msgid ""
"Saṃyojaniyesu, bhikkhave, dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato taṇhā "
"nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"There are things that are prone to being fettered. When you concentrate on "
"the drawbacks of these things, your craving ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.2"
msgid "Taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho;"
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.3"
msgid "upādānanirodhā bhavanirodho;"
msgstr "When grasping ceases, continued existence ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.4"
msgid "bhavanirodhā jātinirodho;"
msgstr "When continued existence ceases, rebirth ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.5"
msgid "jātinirodhā jarāmaraṇaṃ sokaparidevadukkhadomanassupāyāsā nirujjhanti."
msgstr ""
"When rebirth ceases, old age and death, sorrow, lamentation, pain, sadness, "
"and distress cease."

msgctxt "sn12.53:3.6"
msgid "Evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hoti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn12.53:4.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, telañca paṭicca vaṭṭiñca paṭicca telappadīpo jhāyeyya."
msgstr "Suppose an oil lamp depended on oil and a wick to burn."

msgctxt "sn12.53:4.2"
msgid "Tatra puriso na kālena kālaṃ telaṃ āsiñceyya na vaṭṭiṃ upasaṃhareyya."
msgstr "And no-one would pour oil in and adjust the wick from time to time."

msgctxt "sn12.53:4.3"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, telappadīpo purimassa ca upādānassa pariyādānā aññassa "
"ca anupahārā anāhāro nibbāyeyya."
msgstr ""
"As the original fuel is used up and no more is added, the oil lamp would be "
"extinguished due to lack of fuel."

msgctxt "sn12.53:4.4"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, saṃyojaniyesu dhammesu ādīnavānupassino viharato "
"taṇhā nirujjhati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, there are things that are prone to being fettered. When you "
"concentrate on the drawbacks of these things, your craving ceases."

msgctxt "sn12.53:4.5"
msgid "Taṇhānirodhā upādānanirodho … pe …"
msgstr "When craving ceases, grasping ceases. …"

msgctxt "sn12.53:4.6"
msgid "evametassa kevalassa dukkhakkhandhassa nirodho hotī”ti."
msgstr "That is how this entire mass of suffering ceases.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn12.53:4.7"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
